  "description": "A balanced South Indian lunch bowl where legumes, vegetables, and whole grains carry the dish instead of excess fat. Ridge Gourd Dal Kuzhambu with Kodo Millet brings a distinct structure, seasoning pattern, and grain-legume balance to the table.",
  "preparation": "",
  "cooking_steps": [
    "Heat oil in a pot over medium heat. Add cumin and garlic and cook 30 seconds until fragrant but not dark.",
    "Add onion, tomato, turmeric, and vegetable and cook 4 minutes until the tomato softens.",
    "Add the dal, salt, and 500 ml water. Pressure cook for 3 whistles or simmer covered on low heat for 25 minutes until the dal is soft and spoon-coating.",
    "Whisk lightly to break some of the dal while keeping some texture, then serve with the cooked grain."
  ],
